                <br> <br>
                <b>4. Tax Officer portal: </b>Facilitation of a transparent and improved Tax Officer portal for the hierarchical approval and rejection of tax application. This eliminate the problem of ghost or fake tax officers.
                <br> <br>
                <b>5. Established Tax payer History Portal: </b>This solution system provides the tax officers the current and past tax details and history of tax payers, inclusive of tax payer income change.
                <br> <br>
                <b>6. Revenue Code Generator: </b>A Revenue Code Generator assigns unique identifiers to every tax-related transaction. This allows for clear tracking of payments, making it easier to manage and audit tax payments. Taxpayers receive a revenue code upon completing their transactions, which they can use to verify payment or resolve disputes. It ensures that each transaction is recorded accurately and transparently in the tax authority's system.
                <br> <br>
                <b>7. Assessment Management Portal: </b>The Assessment Management Portal allows tax administrators to evaluate and manage tax liabilities for individuals and businesses. Through this portal, tax authorities can calculate taxes based on income, assets, or business activities, ensuring accurate assessments. It also includes the management of tax exemptions, penalties, and payment deadlines, streamlining the assessment process and reducing errors associated with manual calculations.
                <br> <br>
