                <br> <br>
                <b>9. Central Billing System (CBS): </b>The Central Billing System (CBS) consolidates all tax liabilities (personal income tax, property tax, corporate tax, etc.) into a single billing interface for the taxpayer. This system simplifies the taxpayer experience by providing a clear overview of all taxes due, pending, or paid. It reduces administrative complexity and ensures that taxpayers receive accurate and up-to-date bills for all their tax obligations.
                <br> <br>
                <b>10. Pay-As-You-Earn (PAYE) system: </b>The Pay-As-You-Earn (PAYE) system is an automated tax withholding method that allows employers to deduct income tax from employees' salaries and remit it directly to the government. In TAAS, the PAYE system ensures accurate tax calculations and deductions, providing a transparent and streamlined process for both employers and employees. This automation reduces manual errors and increases the efficiency of income tax collection.
                <br> <br>
                <b>11. Capital Portal: </b>The Capital Portal is designed to handle capital taxes, such as taxes on capital gains, property, and investments. It offers specialized tools for taxpayers to report capital income and for tax authorities to assess these earnings and liabilities. The portal ensures that capital-related taxes are processed efficiently and transparently. It also supports the management of asset declarations and investment-related tax obligations, providing a tailored solution for more complex tax scenarios.
                <br> <br>
                <p>Together, these components form a comprehensive TAAS solution that automates tax administration, improves accuracy, enhances compliance, and streamlines the tax experience for both taxpayers and authorities.</p>
